Introduction

Lee Su Jeong (이수정), formely known as Baby Soul (베이비 소울) is a South Korean singer under Woollim Entertainment. She is the leader of the girl group Lovelyz and one half of the unit duo BabySoul+Yoo Jia.

She originally made her solo debut on November 23, 2011 with the digital single "Stranger".

She debuted as the leader of Lovelyz with their first studio album "Girls' Invasion" on November 17, 2014.
